          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
      </math>= $230. Final payment
      (<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
        <msub>
          <mi>P</mi>
          <mi>n</mi>
        </msub>
      </math>) = $280.</dd>
    <dd>Number of payments (n) = 24. Unit-period = 1 month.</dd>
    <dd>Unit-periods per year (w) = 12.</dd>
    <dd>Advance, 1-10-78. First payment, 2-10-78.</dd>
    <dd>From 1-10-78 through 2-10-78 = 1 unit-period. (t = 1; f = 0)</dd>
    <dd>Annual percentage rate (I) = wi = .1090 = 10:90%</dd>
</dl>
<dl>
  <dt><span style="text-decoration: underline">Example (ii):</span> Payments every two months (short first period, irregular
  first payment, and irregular final payment)</dt>
    <dd>Amount advanced (A) = $8000. Regular payment
      (<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
        <msub>
          <mi>P</mi>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </msub>
      </math>) = $449.36.<br />
      Final payment <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
            <mi>P</mi>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
      </math>= $465. Final payment
      (<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
        <msub>
          <mi>P</mi>
